text: Place wise not bad, so far Malay, Indian, this Chinese and another roasted chicken rice stall are good. Long Q if you are after 1130am but still plenty of seats. Down side is not much parking lots.

The drinks shop owner is super rude. I don't understand how can she scold customers when asked to repeat the price of drinks. The tables are dirty. There's only one cleaner and the tables are rarely wiped clean. Thank god for the good food, especially the chicken rice and the Indian stall. Best option would be to tapau and go.
Xing Xing mixed curry rice very expensive. 3 ingredients charge $5. Wonâ€™t buy from this store again.
Had my pack lunch from Authentic Nasi Padang, Lots of dishes to choose from. Nice and it's value for money

Revisited this place after 15yrs. New Malay stall, nasi lemak was good. Xingxing chap chai rice good as well. Used to buy from them everyday veggie etc to bring home to feed my boys. The boss and his sisters have always been very kind.
